description:
"Kennedy" is a news panel show hosted by Kennedy Montgomery. Kennedy Montgomery is a libertarian that you may recognize from 90's MTV, Stossel, and the Independents.

_,-'2_,-'2_,-'2_,-'2_,-'2_,-'2_,-'2_,-'2_,-'2_,-'2

Kennedy does her monologue on Hillary Clinton & the need women feel to vote for her. An anonymous platform called "Whisper" has provided an outlet for the frustration that need could cause.

Kennedy has an especially articulate panel tonight. MICHAEL MALICE, MICHAEL MOYNIHAN, and WILL RAHN are in studio. They kick the night off talking about Hillary and her email troubles, her Bernie troubles, and Carley Fiorna qualifying for the big debate stage. After a quick (hah) commercial break the panel returns to talk about the Trump vs Jeb fight. 

Pete Hegseth is here to judge the 2016 on their foreign policy plans according to his views.

The panel returns to talk about the least friendly cities in the world. Russia has two in the top 5. Boston is 15th. LA is worse than New York. Next up - Can blind people be racist and divorce selfies.

Anointed capitalist pig Jonathan Hoenig is here to talk about the a turbulent stock market.

Nightcap: All day breakfast
